&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; As an Accounting Specialist, you will be responsible for the day-to-day accounting operations of assigned projects, including transaction processing, expense verification, and financial report preparation. You will ensure the accuracy and completeness of financial data, support business decision-making through timely and precise financial analysis, and help maintain a sound financial management framework.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle daily accounting transactions such as expense reimbursements, revenue recognition, and cost accounting, ensuring all records are accurate and compliant.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and analyze monthly, quarterly, and annual financial statements (including balance sheets, income statements, and cash flow statements). Provide management with relevant reports and insights to support decision-making.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in budget preparation and financial forecasting, analyze budget variances, and provide recommendations for improvement.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide accurate financial data and analysis to support departmental and project-level financial planning.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to the optimization of accounting processes and systems to enhance efficiency and accuracy.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in the establishment and maintenance of internal financial control policies to ensure compliance and financial security.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support external audit processes by preparing and providing required financial information and documentation to ensure smooth completion of audits.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficient in &lt;strong&gt;Microsoft Excel&lt;/strong&gt; and familiar with &lt;strong&gt;accounting standards and principles&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience using &lt;strong&gt;financial or accounting software&lt;/strong&gt;; candidates with &lt;strong&gt;accounting certifications&lt;/strong&gt; are preferred.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum of &lt;strong&gt;3 years of accounting or financial experience&lt;/strong&gt; is preferred.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bachelor’s degree or above&lt;/strong&gt; in Accounting, Finance, or a related field is preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are hiring for one of our clients. They are looking for a newly established Registered Agent in the British Virgin Islands (BVI) offering company management services. You will be working as part of a global team with deep expertise in the industry. Their ambition is to build one of the best corporate service providers in the industry. We are looking for dynamic team members who bring a background in corporate governance, legal or accounting. If this sounds like you, we want to talk to you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking an Account Manager to join our team in Hong Kong to lead our client&amp;nbsp;services function.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the transfer-in process for our clients and perform client on-boarding&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with the Compliance Manager on KYC procedures&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as key liaison with our Hong Kong based clients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work with BVI team to prepare certificates of incumbency, good standing, and manage changes to directors, members, and beneficial owners&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee regulatory filings such as economic substance and maintain accurate customer records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Keep databases updated and coordinate with Finance for invoicing&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage transactions on VIRRGIN and liaise with clients, intermediaries, and internal teams&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft minutes and resolutions to support client transactions&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are looking for someone who&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Degree qualification in Business Administration, Law, Accounting, Corporate Governance or other business-related disciplines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Minimum 5 years’ corporate services experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication skills in English and Chinese (Cantonese and/or Mandarin)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicative, responsive and good interpersonal skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong analytical skills, detail-oriented, and able to meet deadlines&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Tech-Savvy. Interest or experience in coding is a bonus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p data-path-to-node=&quot;2&quot;&gt;We are a provider of crypto-integrated software solutions, dedicated to bridging the gap between sophisticated blockchain technology and everyday utility. Our mission is to scale our reach through a robust, decentralized ecosystem of advocates. As our &lt;strong&gt;Affiliate Network Builder&lt;/strong&gt;, you will be the lead architect of our partnership engine, identifying, recruiting, and managing a high-performance network of affiliates and influencers who will champion our products to a global audience.&lt;/p&gt;
